# No invented facts

## Rule
Unknown facts are marked `TBD — <specific question>`. Never assert a fact you cannot cite from a `.cursor/` file, `efp-ai-knowledge-base/` file, or directly observed source code.

## Why
Confidence is cheap; accuracy is expensive. The brain, the ADR process, and every downstream agent depend on being able to trust recorded facts without re-verifying. One invented claim propagates.

## Constraints
- Every non-trivial claim in a generated artifact carries a source reference (`<repo>/.cursor/...` or `efp-ai-knowledge-base/...` or `source:<path>:<line>`).
- When in doubt, prefer `TBD — <question>` over a plausible guess.
- Agents that produce plans or reviews must explicitly note "no evidence" when a field cannot be filled.

## Examples

### Good
> `auth-provider: TBD — which provider does fb-shipper-frontend consume? (fy-iam-go inferred from Skipper routing, not confirmed)`

### Bad
> `auth-provider: fy-iam-go` (asserted without evidence for a repo whose `.cursor/` was thinly covered).

## Related
- Skills: all.
- Agents: every agent enforces this on its own output.
- ADRs: none.
